    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I found out I'm able to add a _map scale_ and a _rose_ for a **geographic** projection:\r\n```python\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(region=[0, 5, 55, 56], projection=\"S2.5/90/2i\", frame=[\"a+ue\", \"wsEN\"], rose='jMC+w0.5i')\r\nfig.show()\r\n```\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5186265/101072386-3d086f80-359e-11eb-9c90-8910f52ab211.png)\r\n\r\n```\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(region=[0, 5, 55, 56], projection=\"S2.5/90/2i\", frame=[\"a+ue\", \"wsEN\"], map_scale='jMC+c1+w100k+f+l')\r\nfig.show()\r\n```\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5186265/101072414-48f43180-359e-11eb-91e0-c38d536e1311.png)\r\n\r\nAnd I could add a map scale in a **cartesian** projection\r\n```\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(region='0/1000/1000/2000+ue', projection='x1:10000', frame=[\"ag\", \"wsEN\"], map_scale='jMC+w500e+l')\r\nfig.show()\r\n```\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5186265/101072427-4f82a900-359e-11eb-8851-acc80082d3a4.png)\r\n\r\nBut how do I add a _rose_ in a **cartesian** projection?\r\nSince the following is giving me a blank plot:\r\n```\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(region='0/1000/1000/2000+ue', projection='x1:10000', frame=[\"ag\", \"wsEN\"], rose='jMC+w0.2i+l')\r\nfig.show()\r\n```\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5186265/101072444-57424d80-359e-11eb-8061-c64d0bb7e0e7.png)\r\n\r\n",
